## Analysis of the Main Target Image

The target structure consists of 9 blocks arranged in a house-like formation. It has 1 main layer with some blocks appearing to be placed on one side of the structure.

Components:
- 3 green rectangular blocks (2 tall vertical rectangles on the sides and 1 horizontal rectangle at the back)
- 2 orange cylindrical blocks in the center
- 4 orange triangular/wedge-shaped blocks (forming roof-like elements on the sides and top)

Spatial relationships:
- The center of the structure has two vertical orange cylindrical blocks placed side by side
- A green vertical rectangular block is positioned on each side of the cylindrical blocks
- Three orange triangular/wedge blocks are placed on the sides (one on the left and two on the right) 
- One orange triangular block is placed on top of the cylinders forming a roof-like structure
- A green horizontal rectangular block appears to be at the back of the structure

## Selected Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on my analysis of the target structure, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:

1. Green rectangular blocks:
   - Block with index 2 (vertical green rectangle) - needed twice
   - Block with index 4 (horizontal green rectangle) - needed once

2. Orange cylindrical blocks:
   - Block with index 5 (vertical orange cylinder) - needed twice

3. Orange triangular/wedge blocks:
   - Block with index 11 (orange triangular wedge) - needed once
   - Block with index 13 (orange triangular wedge) - needed once
   - Block with index 15 (orange triangular wedge) - needed once
   - Block with index 16 (orange triangular wedge) - needed once

## Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 4
   Step2: Move block with index 2
   Step3: Move block with index 2
   Step4: Move block with index 5
   Step5: Move block with index 5
   Step6: Move block with index 11
   Step7: Move block with index 13
   Step8: Move block with index 15
   Step9: Move block with index 16
}
```
